review_blob:
My lord what an understood brew!  Sit back, take a sip, think. reflect, enjoy...! this is a qualiy brew folks! A rare, and potent brew. Malty and slightly sweet, then liqueur on the finish but not to much! think style folks...this beer fits the style. Wonderful! 

Kulmbacher eisbock is sweet, then liqueur on the finish. Wonderful!
not my idea of a holiday brew at all. that said its not a bad beer. a bit thin but nice hops and quite refreshing.

malty as hell! a good thing for my tastes. this seasons batch doesnt taste quite as good as the last, perhaps its because im now used to drinking higher caliber beers? dont get me wrong,  great taste, just not as good as last year.
poured a rich head, deep amber color. citrus is present as well as more noticable hops than usual in this batch.
very drinkable.winter lager is their best in my opinion though. get it while it lasts.

didnt realize this was bottle conditioned until after the pour. a deep golden hazy pour. aroma was citrus and hops and something i just cant place. was surprized at the smoothness of this beer, i assummed it would be hop overkill at 90 IBU but perhaps the smoothest big beer ive had in this style to date! A very nice beer.

beer_name: Flying Dog Horn Dog Barley Wine

review_blob:
very surprised!  no longer a fan of golden beers until this one passed my lips! ummmm.... a minor taste of citrus and perhaps a slight bubblegum tone to it. another confusing beer actually! 
id say grab a four pack and enjoy because i think you certainly will enjoy this one...even if NOT a fan of golden brews! try it.

wow... i love trying beers new to me. this is a real experience indeed! poured with a thin head but then i pour all beers very slow, even so a lot of floaties were seen.  i detected a slight bannana scent at first but then more of a nutty/malty scent. another beer that for me is a bit more carbonated than i would like, but the overall flavor and complexity of this one counteracts the carbonation. damn, its too expensive, about $5.95 a bottle but for a great treat every once in a while well worth it in my opinion! first timers seeing this bottle at the store may pass it up because of the lame/plain looking lable....but hey, dont pass this one up! grab at least two of these! in this case boring bottle= exciting drinking!
UPDATED: AUG 9, 2004

review_blob: This smells and tastes much like the aventinus wiezen bock, only more noticable alcohol taste, mainly on the finish.  i prefer the 8% weizen bock but still very good if you like big alcohol beers!

Amber color and small head. Nice aroma, maltly, fruity, and a tiny bit of hop presence in this one although tiny.  Almost replaced sam adams boston lager for me but I like flying dog  pale ale better than this lager.
beer_name: Flying Dog Old Scratch Amber Lager

review_blob: Very thin buit thats the style! Poured a very ligh clean goldned color, mild head that vanished rapidly. Seems all beer from this company has that slight citrus flavor. A drinkable beer but not my style.
beer_name: Flying Dog Tire Bite Golden Ale

review_blob: Light amber color with hoppy aroma. Head diminished rather quickly. Like most Flying Dog beers, a bit on the watery side. The pale ale is much better imo but still not a bad beer at all.
Hints of chocolate in this one. A bit thin but very drinkabe and a good price to boot.

very dark amber color with a good head. very malty tasting and just the right amount of hops. spiced slightly but not overdone. i think this is adams best beer to date and wish they would make it year-round! not easy to find in my area but worth the hunt. this is a very good beer.
dark golden color with very unusual aroma. decent head, slightly malty and sweet. could benefit from more malt flavor. overall a pretty decent beer.
